HEADWORD: Foot poundal
<hw>Foot" pound`al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A unit of
energy or work, equal to the work done in moving a body through one foot
against the force of one poundal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

